From f0dcda2ca510c69cb92031a3a0d825766fcefdf7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 18 Jun 2026 09:43:35 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Make the kick harder: triode saturator, phase locking, ADAA
 wavefolder
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Three improvements from the research document to achieve competitive hardness:

1. Asymmetric triode saturator (Shaper::Tube, replaces plain tanh):
   f(x) = (x-q)/(1-exp(-k(x-q))) + q/(1-exp(kq))
   With bias > 0 the curve is asymmetric around the operating point q,
   generating even harmonics alongside the odd ones. This is the difference
   between a thin, bright hardstyle tone and a thick, aggressive rawstyle body.
   Output bounded via tanh; numerically stable near xq=0 and q=0 via L'Hopital.

2. Phase locking on trigger (osc.rs):
   Oscillator now resets to phase = 0.25 (π/2, the sine peak) instead of 0
   (zero-crossing). Every trigger delivers maximum amplitude on the first sample,
   giving a consistent, punchy sub-impact regardless of retrigger timing.

3. First-order ADAA on the sine wavefolder (WaveShaper struct):
   Replaces naive hard-fold with ADAA using the closed-form antiderivative of
   sin(x*π/2): F(x) = -(2/π)*cos(x*π/2). Output = (F(x)-F(x_prev))/(x-x_prev)
   with midpoint fallback when consecutive samples are too close. Eliminates
   the aliasing products that made the raw folder sound gritty at high drive.

WaveShaper is now a stateful struct; lib.rs and render.rs use it instead of
the stateless shape() function (which is kept for the editor waveform preview).

Co-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
